      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>If methanol rather than water is added at the end of a Hell–Volhard–Zelinskii reaction, an ester rather than an acid is produced. Show how you would carry out the following transformation, and propose a mechanism for the ester-forming step.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdlVYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a31b4531993ba9f24f835cf0007698d4c6650cce/OChem_22_04_003.jpg\" alt=\"3-methyl pentanoic acid reacts with unknown reagent represented by question mark to form six-carbon chain with carbonyl group at C 2, bromine at C 3, and methyl at C 4.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "The intermediate <i>α</i>-bromo acid bromide undergoes a nucleophilic acyl substitution reaction with methanol to give an <i>α</i>-bromo ester."
        }
      ],
      "community_solutions": []
    }
